description: With no one party winning a majority, there could be lengthy negotiations to establish a government.
title: Irish general election: Parties turn their focus towards government
title_page: Irish general election: Parties turn their focus towards government - BBC News
maintext: "If you had asked me in '97 I'd have said there was no chance. I'd now say in the next decade it does seem to me possible because of the way that Brexit is going to be engineered and the way it is going to be implemented," he told The Nolan Show.
